<TEXT>
police broke up opposition party sitins at 
eight city halls in guerrero state on tuesday and at least three 
police and two activists were killed government and party 
officials said 
the centerleft democratic revolutionary party had paralyzed 20 
of the southwestern states 75 city governments for three months 
protesting alleged fraud in dec 3 elections 
gov francisco ruiz massieu said five people were killed in the 
police actions 
now peace has been restored ruiz massieu said in a 
television interview 
at a mexico city news conference held by eight guerrero state 
democratic revolutionary party leaders party spokesman ricardo 
pascoe said we are confronting state terrorists that want 
repression 
government officials said about 200 state police and cadets were 
called out to remove 350 people 
opposition party leaders said about 80 supporters were injured 
and 30 arrested 
two party members were reportedly killed when police broke up 
the sitin at the ometepec city hall about 50 miles southeast of 
acapulco guerrero party chief rosalio wences reza said 
two policemen were killed with automatic weapons when they tried 
to protesters at the nearby cruz grande town hall guerrero state 
government spokesman francisco javier rangel said by telephone 
federal highway police commander mario juarez servin reported 
another officer killed in the confrontations the government news 
agency notimex said 
the state called on police to act because of what happened 
feb 27 when party members tried to take over the acapulco and 
zihuatanejo airports the state government said in a statement 
three people were killed in confrontations when police stopped 
protesters on airport roads last week in the resort cities of 
acapulco and ixtapa near zihuatenejo 
rangel said the state government is concerned about the states 
image because tourism is its main source of income and employment 
tourism is mexicos thirdlargest source of foreign exchange 
state legislators agreed tuesday to measures allowing 
powersharing in seven guerrero communities where city halls are 
still blockaded a state news release said 
rangel said he didnt know if more police actions would be taken 
to end blockades 
