a teenager snubbed by youths playing a pickup 
basketball game returned in a van with a shotgun and sprayed the 
group with blasts of birdshot wounding 10 police said monday 
none of the injuries were serious although one of the players 
was hit in the head and another in the back police said the rest 
were hit in the arms legs and upper bodies 
all 10 were released after treatment at jackson memorial 
hospital 
police late monday arrested eric leon keaton 19 of miami on 
charges of attempted firstdegree murder and use of a firearm in 
the commission of a felony in the incident said spokesman armando 
villorin 
the group which included two juniorvarsity high school 
players was playing sunday on a court sunday outside an elementary 
school when the youth a stranger asked to play but was told he 
couldnt get into the game witnesses told police 
the teen left but returned a few minutes later riding in the 
