<TEXT>
italian communists spurred by the collapse of 
communism in eastern europe want to set their party on a new course 
this week one their leader believes can ultimately unite italys 
fractured political left 
an 1100delegate extraordinary congress of the italian 
communist party meets wednesday through saturday in bologna to 
consider party leader achille occhettos proposal for a rebirth of 
the largest communist party in the west 
occhetto is calling for in effect creating a broad new party 
that will seek to unite italys leftist parties under a single 
umbrella and effectively challenge the dominant christian democrats 
the communists are italys secondlargest party but have been 
kept out of the national government for more than 42 years 
despite bitter opposition from the partys old guard occhettos 
plan seems to have the support of about 67 percent of the 
delegates thats more than enough votes to assure him success and 
perhaps lead the party to adopt a new name and drop the hammer and 
sickle from its symbol 
in november just days after the berlin wall crumbled occhetto 
stunned italian communists when without consulting other party 
leaders he suggested the party change its name and set out on a 
new street to unify the forces of progress 
the partys central committee instead of adopting his proposal 
called for the extraordinary congress and decided to leave the 
decision to the delegates in bologna 
for occhetto the rebirth of the party is a gamble aimed at 
reversing its sagging political fortunes the christian democrats 
have led or dominated all italian governments since world war ii 
occhetto hopes a rebirth of the 14 millionmember party would 
move it closer to the ideas of the greens the radical party and 
liberal catholics thus creating a new political force 
divisions among leftists have caused the permanent victory of 
the christian democrats he said in november 
occhetto also would like that force eventually to include 
italys socialist party the countrys third largest 
but the socialists dont feel the same pressures they have been 
coalition partners with the christian democrats for the last decade 
socialist leader bettino craxi watching the steady electoral 
slide of the italian communists has campaigned to lead his party 
past the communists in the polls if he succeeds the socialists 
will become the second largest party and the de facto leader of the 
italian left 
