woodside had asked armstrong to resign late last year but 
armstrong refused and sought support from board members art 
dealers and donors supporters praised him in a petition signed 
last week by more than 200 people 
some reports said he had made some antisemitic remarks but one 
board member robert w wilson told the new york times last month 
the alleged remarks were being excluded from any consideration of 
armstrongs future 
a scholar in american art told the times in december that the 
museum had exhibited too much contemporary schlock and too many 
superficial exhibitions of meaningful american artists the 
scholar declined to be identified 
another problem concerned a proposed 375 million addition that 
would double the museums size the plan unveiled in 1985 drew 
criticism because it proposed to wrap the new structure around the 
original museum which was designed by modernist architect marcel 
breuer the plans were revised 
woodside said a search committee will choose a new director 
