other opposition leaders to abandon their attacks on the sales tax 
given the comfortable majority his party won in feb 18 
parliamentary elections 
opposition parties unsuccessfully based their campaigns in last 
months lower house election on calls to abolish the sales tax 
which along with a series of sex and money scandals eroded public 
support for the governing party and contributed to its loss of 
