<TEXT>
chancellor helmut kohl has agreed to 
formally state support for a treaty on polands western border 
without asking for concessions from the poles his chief of staff 
said today 
the announcement followed a crucial meeting of kohls coalition 
government which was seriously divided over the chancellors 
previous handling of the border issue 
rudolf seiters kohls chief of staff said the coalition 
partners had agreed to introduce a resolution in parliament on 
thursday favoring a treaty recognizing the current borders with 
poland 
seiters said the resolution would not include kohls demands 
made friday that any such treaty be linked with assurances by 
poland to honor its 1953 decision not to seek war reparations from 
germany and its pledge last year to guarantee the ethnic rights of 
its german minority 
it was not clear whether the resolution would state as kohl 
has many times insisted that only the government of a united 
germany can have final say on the border issue 
kohls previous pronouncements on the border issue have angered 
the poles and resulted in severe criticism at home even from his 
