<TEXT>
as afghanistans defense minister maj 
gen shah nawaz tanai was supposed to lead the fight against moslem 
guerrillas instead he may have plotted with them against 
president najib 
the attempted coup tuesday illustrated the simultaneous 
challenges najib faces in trying to pacify enemies in his own party 
and end the 12yearold civil war 
kabul radio said tanai who became defense minister about 18 
months ago plotted with fundamentalist guerrilla leader gulbuddin 
hekmatyar such an alliance would one of convenience not ideology 
given tanais long advocacy of harsh methods against the guerrillas 
by linking tanai to hekmatyar the government may be trying to 
set the stage for the defense ministers final disgrace 
in recent months najib increasingly has presented hekmatyar as 
the personification of evil while depicting other guerrilla leaders 
and field commanders as more rational and welcome to join his 
sovietbacked government 
hekmatyar has become increasingly estranged from his fellow 
guerrilla leaders rejecting their political leadership and killing 
some of their followers 
najib has promoted tanai both in the government and communist 
party even though the general has a reputation for active 
opposition 
its become a familiar scenario since the party took control by 
coup and assassination in april 1978 give your enemies power in 
hopes of buying obedience then try to keep them from overthrowing 
you 
afghan sources from both sides of the party and civil war say 
tanai has been involved in at least the last three of five known 
coup attempts since najib became president in december 1986 the 
two most recent ones occurred in july and december 
tanai is from the party faction called khalq or masses and 
najib represents the parcham or flag faction parcham 
generally is less hawkish than khalq especially when it comes to 
making political overtures to the guerrillas 
najib loyalists say the president has begun an effort to change 
the party even its name to make it more acceptable to the 
insurgents the afghan people and such foreign critics as the 
united states the partys official name is the peoples democratic 
party of afghanistan 
such overtures generally have been lost on the islamic 
fundamentalist guerrillas who refuse to deal with a godless 
party 
tanai believed to be in his mid40s is known as a foe of any 
concessions to the insurgents or modification of the partys 
marxist origins najib recently has sought to portray the party as 
a defender of islam and champion of a freemarket economy 
the general comes from the tanai district near khost in southern 
afghanistan and takes his surname from his home region 
he is a member of the party politburo whose membership is said 
to be 14 tanai became defense minister sometime in 1988 but as 
often happens in afghanistan his appointment apparently was not 
announced 
when najib changed his cabinet in february 1989 after soviet 
military forces were withdrawn tanai remained in his post 
an afghan source in new delhi said travelers arriving in the 
indian capital monday reported that tanai had installed his 
ministry in the darulaman palace on kabuls southwestern outskirts 
and that it bristled with big guns and antennas 
he said the travelers spoke of widespread rumors in kabul over 
the weekend that tanai was planning a coup the source like the 
others spoke on condition of anonymity 
najibs official residence and office complex arg palace is in 
the heart of kabul both palaces were used by king zahir shah who 
