<TEXT>
workers at the three mile island nuclear 
plant began shutting down the unit 1 reactor tuesday after plant 
monitors detected higherthannormal amounts of radioactivity being 
vented into the atmosphere 
state federal and plant officials said there was no danger to 
the public the releases were not detected by radiation monitors 
located off the island which is about 10 miles south of harrisburg 
also tuesday the unit 3 reactor at the peach bottom nuclear 
power plant in york county near the maryland border was shut down 
because of a mechanical problem with the systems generator 
officials said unit 2 had been shut down last week for maintenance 
gpu nuclear corp which operates tmi said officials believe 
the problem stemmed from a small water leak between the nuclear and 
nonnuclear sides of the plant under federal license requirements 
tmi must shut down if there is a confirmed leak of more than 6 
gallons per hour 
although the leak appeared to be at a rate of 1 gallon per 
minute gpu officials said they decided to immediately shut down 
the plant instead of going through a process to confirm the actual 
rate the plant could have continued to operate until the leak was 
confirmed to be 6 gallons per hour they said 
the shutdown is a precautionary measure and no emergency 
condition exists said mary wells a gpu spokeswoman 
the higherthannormal levels of radiation were detected by a 
monitor in the plants steam system radiation left the plant 
through a vent on that system 
doug bedell a gpu spokesman said only a fraction of one 
millirem of radiation was released over a threehour period he 
said a chest xray would equal about 10 millirems of radiation a 
millirem is a unit of measurement 
karl abraham a spokesman for the nuclear regulatory commission 
said the leak at tmi at a rate of about 1 gallon per minute was 
detected shortly before 830 am 
workers began shutting the reactor down shortly after 9 am 
plant officials said 
susan woods a spokeswoman for the state department of 
environmental resources said the agency had not detected any 
abovenormal radiation levels offsite 
the plant is going into normal shutdown they are doing it 
manually she said if there was a serious problem it would 
have automatically shut down 
the plant had been operating at 75 percent capacity it was 
recently out of service for two months for maintenance and to 
replenish its nuclear fuel 
we dont know when it will be up again bedell said we 
need to determine the nature and source of these leaks before we 
would consider starting up the plant 
tmi 1s sister plant unit 2 was the site of the nations worst 
commercial nuclear accident in 1979 a combination of human and 
mechanical errors led to the draining of protective cooling water 
from the plants radioactive gases were released into the 
atmosphere unit 1 was undamaged in the accident 
a spokesman for philadelphia electric co which owns peach 
bottom did not immediately return a phone call for comment 
