underground 
we think the vandals get tired of seeing their individual 
trademarks cleaned off and cant be bothered to keep going back to 
renew their scribbles he said 
london underground operates the 237mile system and its 268 
stations which londoners call the tube 
removing graffiti from trains stations and other buildings on 
the subway costs more than 32 million a year and some stations 
suffer as many as 700 attacks a month 
a cleaning company specializing in graffiti removal was hired in 
august on a 656000 oneyear contract to work on a group of 15 
stations at the northern end of the metropolitan line its cleaners 
aimed to get rid of the daubing within 10 hours of staff reporting 
attacks 
