the town meeting had all the makings of a 
lowbudget soap opera a bitter 12year feud between families a 
battle over selling booze and a question about who should govern 
first and foremost voters went to the polls tuesday to decide 
whether the towns only general store mh shermans owned by 
marion and john pelton should be allowed to continue selling beer 
and wine 
a rejection could force residents to travel six miles or more to 
buy beer and wine making rupert one of only six dry towns in 
vermont rupert which borders new york in southern vermont was a 
dry town until voters narrowly approved the sale of beer and wine 
in 1981 
