fairly remote that enrile would flee the country but the panel 
said it made no determination on whether rebellion and murder could 
be charged together 
enriles lawyers argued that a 1956 supreme court decision 
nullified the joint charge one justice speaking on condition of 
anonymity said the court would meet in a few weeks to review the 
1956 ruling 
lawyers for enrile said they expect the court to decide on the 
dual charge within the month 
late tuesday enriles lawyers presented his release order to 
authorities and he walked out of the suburban northern police 
headquarters where he has been jailed since last week 
like a jailed bird that has just been set free ill fly away 
happily enrile said while signing autographs for police officers 
before boarding his bulletproof van 
in a radio interview wednesday enrile called the case against 
him unbelievable he said the courts decision to release him 
without deciding the merits of the charge was done so as not to 
embarrass the government 
i am praying for our president for enlightenment enrile 
said she is in a very difficult situation because she does 
not know everything that is happening around her 
after a threehour hearing tuesday 10 justices voted in favor 
of granting 4650 bail each to enrile and two codefendants hotel 
owner rebecco panlilio and his wife four other justices voted to 
deny bail and one abstained 
rebellion is punishable by six to 12 years in prison and 
defendants are eligible for bail murder carries a life sentence 
and bail is not allowed 
enrile and six others were indicted feb 27 in the dec 19 coup 
attempt in which at least 113 people were killed and more than 600 
injured enrile denies any role 
some of enriles colleagues in the senate criticized how the 
government handled the case 
sen ernesto maceda a lawyer said enrile should have been 
charged only with rebellion 
then maybe there would not have been any problems in turning 
enrile into a martyr and a hero the result of the administrations 
decision to file a complex case is really bad maceda said 
enrile was charged after witnesses claimed they saw former lt 
col gregorio gringo honasan a rebellion leader at enriles 
home on the first day of the coup attempt the panlilios were also 
allegedly at the enrile home on dec 1 
during the hearing about 200 enrile sympathizers gathered 
outside the courthouse carrying signs reading justice for 
enrile a group of antienrile demonstrators rallied at another 
gate and hundreds of armed police stood guard in the building and 
nearby streets 
inside one of enriles lawyers former supreme court justice 
serafin cuevas argued that the detention of the opposition senator 
is illegal and unconstitutional 
we say so because the information under which he was charged 
and sought to be prosecuted is for an offense that does not exist 
in our law books cuevas added 
solicitor gen francisco chavez argued that the law does allow 
for a dual charge if a single act involves two or more grave or 
less grave felonies 
he recommended that the court reconsider the 1956 ruling 
what we have here is disgruntled members of the armed 
forces military adventurists plain and simply power grabbers 
as defense minister enrile led the february 1986 mutiny that 
precipitated the people power revolution that swept mrs aquino 
to power he was fired nine months later after a failed coup by his 
followers 
