texacos 50year love affair with the 
metropolitan opera is being celebrated on both radio and television 
in concerts highlighting memorable moments from past performances 
on radio a live gala will take the place of the regular 
saturday afternoon opera broadcast march 10 on the 
texacometropolitan opera radio network more than a dozen singers 
and six conductors will perform arias ensembles and overtures that 
have been favorites during the 50 years of texaco sponsorship 
on television the public broadcasting service is offering 
great moments from the met culled from the nearly 50 operas 
televised since 1977 thanks to funding from texaco the show is 
being made available to pbs stations for use anytime during the 
march 1990 pledge drive 
great moments is packed with as much vocal talent as anyone 
could ask for luciano pavarotti and placido domingo are 
represented twice each and so are kathleen battle jessye norman 
and samuel ramey all are in excellent voice as they perform arias 
or duets from favorite roles 
but somehow the whole adds up to considerably less than the 
sum of its parts 
part of the problem is that we cant appreciate these artists 
fully just hearing snippets of their work worse even the snippets 
are interrupted by voiceovers as the performers give us their 
mostly superfluous views on what the characters they are portraying 
are all about 
im going to do this opera until i cant pavarotti tells us 
eagerly but uninformatively about donizettis lelisir 
damore miss norman discussing the title role of strauss 
