nearly lost a few toes on conventional bedframes himself but 
would i go out and buy that it would take a pretty significant 
experience to take that leap of faith 
disappointed expectations arise sometimes from unrealistic 
hopes say patent and marketing experts some inventors wildly 
inflate the value of an idea that makes a product only marginally 
more salable 
but graff persists looking for new marketing outlets 
ive lost money so far but you dont plan on making money 
this far into the project he says im convinced its a good 
product and once the consumer gets ahold of it 
