the great hitchock comes to mind he loved outlandish 
situations such as the chase across mount rushmore in north by 
northwest in bad influence two brothers try to dispose of a 
body in los angeles famed la brea tar pits the films theme is 
basic hitchcock normal citizen finds himself enmeshed in a deadly 
game 
james spader is a marketing analyst successful in his work and 
engaged to the rich beautiful kathleen wilhoite his life is 
wellordered until an encounter in a beach bar with lowe a 
ruthless charmer who takes over spaders life teaching him to 
outfox his office rivals and introducing him to a dangerous beauty 
lisa zane 
lowe introduces spader to fast living drugs and los angeles 
undergound nightlife then to criminal acts spader restores his 
senses and tries to escape but to his horror he becomes involved 
in murder 
bad influence might have been just another exercise in the 
destructive fastlane life of los angeles but david koepp has 
fashioned a screenplay filled with unexpected turns and shocks and 
curtis hanson directed in taut style aided immeasurably by robert 
elswits stunning photography 
spader sex lies and videotape draws an impressive 
characterization of a man in a quagmire lowe whose previous work 
has seemed vapid and colorless corrects that impression this time 
out he is profoundly evil as the protean drifter 
steve tisch directed the epic production which bears a 
welldeserved r for nudity sex violence drugs and language 
running time 110 minutes 
</TEXT>
