<TEXT>
hes known as the father of financial futures 
but after 23 years as a leader of the chicago mercantile exchange 
leo melamed says hes stepping down to spend more time with his 
real family 
theyve always taken short change in my obligations and 
responsibilities and they always get left behind melamed said 
of his wife bette and three grown children 
the 57yearold chairman of the mercs executive committee made 
the surprise announcement monday telling a news conference he 
wanted to smell the flowers along the way while i can still smell 
something 
his resignation becomes effective at the end of the year the 
merc board has not yet named his successor 
the polishborn melamed a tireless innovator and cheerleader 
for the futures industry said he was not retiring for health 
reasons or because of the continuing federal investigation of 
trading fraud at the merc and the larger chicago board of trade 
the worlds two biggest futures markets 
he said he planned to continue trading to devote more time to 
his trading firm dellsher investment company inc and to do more 
writing melamed published a sciencefiction novel the tenth 
planet in 1987 and said he has finished a sequel 
melamed also said he expects the merc to launch its globex 
electronic trading system one of his pet projects by june 30 
implementation of globex originally slated for the spring of 
1989 has been delayed in part because of trouble in getting 
approval from the japanese government for japanese companies to 
trade on the system 
its going to create a real vacuum john damgard president 
of the futures industry association a washingtonbased trade 
group said of melameds pending departure 
under the leadership of the charismatic and outspoken melamed 
the chicago merc pioneered trading of financial futures that allow 
investors to hedge bets on the future prices of currencies and 
stock indexes 
before melamed futures exchanges were best known for trading 
agricultural commodities eggs livestock and pork bellies in the 
mercs case futures are contracts to buy and sell commodities and 
financial instruments in the future at prices agreed upon when the 
contract is bought 
with the help of milton friedman a nobel laureate in economics 
the merc introduced the first foreign currency futures in 1972 
they gave investors the chance to bet on future values of the west 
german mark the swiss franc the canadian dollar and the japanese 
yen 
the contracts fueled explosive growth in the industry and 
brought futures greater respectability in the financial world 
financial products such as currency bond and stockindex 
futures accounted for more than 60 percent of the 2674 million 
futures contracts traded last year in the united states in 1970 
us futures trading volume totaled 136 million contracts 
the growth also brought controversy though many investors 
blamed computerized trading strategies that use stockindex futures 
for accelerating the plunge of the stock market during the october 
1987 crash 
melamed was one of the staunchest defenders of stockindex 
futures and his lobbying helped fend off congressional efforts to 
impose curbs on the market 
melamed was chairman of the merc from 1969 until 1971 when he 
stepped aside to become chairman of a new affiliate set up to trade 
financial futures the international monetary market 
in 1976 the imm merged with the merc and melamed became 
chairman of the combined institutions 
a year later the merc board created the office of special 
counsel to the board and named melamed to the position and to the 
position of chairman of the executive committee 
melamed began working as a runner at the merc in the early 1950s 
while working his way through law school he became an exchange 
member in 1954 and a member of the exchanges board of governors in 
1967 
</TEXT>
