merger of mitsui bank ltd and taiyo kobe bank ltd paving the way 
for the establishment in april of the second largest bank in japan 
as measured by deposits 
masaaki tsuchida head of the ministrys banking bureau handed 
the letter of approval personally to mitsui bank president kenichi 
suematsu and taiyo kobe bank president yasuo matsushita 
the new bank to be called the mitsui taiyo kobe bank ltd will 
be the second largest following daiichi kangyo bank ltd when it 
opens for business on april 1 
