the producers of perrier sparkling water began 
resupplying their distributors today three weeks after ordering 
the recall of 160 million bottles worldwide 
the company said bottles marked with the words nouvelle 
production would be available wednesday in french stores and 
throughout most of europe canada and the eastern united states by 
early april 
the new bottled water will be available in the western united 
states by april 22 perrier said 
us importers plan to spend 25 million on a marketing campaign 
aimed first at building anticipation of the return of the drink 
that became a status symbol in the 1980s and then to rebuild sales 
of the topselling imported bottled water brand in the united 
states 
ads scheduled to run wednesday in 22 majormarket or national 
newspapers will use the theme perrier worth waiting for 
a companion radio campaign also will be used in the 15 biggest 
markets that takes a humorous approach using the format of the 
perrier news network detailing reported sightings of perrier in 
various locations 
a new advertising campaign is being prepared for use when the 
beverage is in wide circulation across the country 
ronald v davis president and chief executive of the perrier 
group of america told a news conference in new york that he 
expects the first bottles of the new perrier to start appearing in 
new york in early april 
he said the beverage will begin showing up in other us markets 
over the next 60 to 90 days he said it will take until the end of 
summer to make all varieties of perrier available throughout the 
united states 
davis declined to estimate what the cost of the recall has been 
but said perrier normally could have expected sales of 30 million 
during the four months it will have been either off the market or 
in limited distribution 
but at the same time he said retailers have given about half of 
the shelf space that perrier would have occupied to other brands 
distributed by perrier group including poland spring arrowhead 
and calistoga 
the recall was announced feb 14 after traces of benzene a 
cancercausing chemical were found in perrier samples in several 
countries including the united states canada west germany the 
netherlands and denmark 
benzene a naturally occurring chemical used in cleaning 
solvents entered perriers bottling line when workers failed to 
replace a filter the company said 
perrier said today that an international team of experts using 
extremely sophisticated techniques would ensure that the 
mineral water henceforth was pure 
our task now is to serve the consumer whoser patience 
confidence and understanding has deeply touched us said 
perriers president gustave leven who founded the company in 1948 
the company said it had commissioned a survey in france 
britain the united states and canada indicating that four out of 
five perrier drinkers would start buying the sparkling water again 
as soon as it became available 
the company said it had not yet been able to calculate the 
worldwide cost of the resupply program 
in france unlike other countries the recall was voluntary 
some supermarket chains cleared their shelves of the product while 
other shopowners continued to sell it 
