world exports of coffee jumped by nearly 25 
percent last year after international controls on sales were 
abolished in july the international coffee organization said 
tuesday 
exports to all destinations in the last half of 1989 totaled 
396 million bags compared with 319 million in the comparative 
period of 1988 the organization reported 
one bag equals 60 kilos or 132 pounds 
the julydecember exports brought total sales for 1989 to 732 
million bags up from 652 million in 1988 when the coffee 
organizations system of export quotas was limiting supplies to 
prop up prices 
the quota system was abandoned on july 4 when producer and 
consumer member governments failed to agree on the terms for its 
continuation 
