<TEXT>
misubishi corp said tuesday it was negotiating 
with west germanys daimlerbenz group to form a series of joint 
ventures between the industrial giants in aerospace electronics 
and other fields 
if completed an agreement would unite japan and west germanys 
two largest business groups giving mitsubishi a toehold in a 
united european economic comunity in 1992 and daimlerbenz access 
to japanese technology 
top executives from mitsubishi and daimlerbenz held talks on 
expanding their cooperation last weekend in singapore mitsubishi 
said in a statement tuesday 
mitsubishi said the areas explored included highgrowth 
industries such as aerospace electronics and the service sector 
that would benefit from development on a global scale and make 
effective use of the skills of both groups 
japanese newspapers reported wednesday that the companies had 
signed an agreement to pursue cooperation in many areas including 
mounting a challenge on us dominance of aerospace technology 
there was a farreaching exchange of ideas about ways to 
expand the relationship beyond the automotive sector where 
mercedes benz and mitsubishi motors corp have enjoyed close 
ties mitsubishi said 
the statement said senior managers from mitsubishi and 
daimlerbenz expressed pleasure at having gained greater 
familiarity with each other and agreed to hold further meetings in 
due course 
mitsubishi spokesman kyosuke mori said the executives had agreed 
to meet once a year and he expected the next meeting would occur 
in 1991 
the companies both make motor vehicles and electronics equipment 
and are active in the aviation and space fields 
mori said the four mitsubishi companies and the four 
daimlerbenz companies whose executives attended the meeting were 
roughly comparable 
they were mitsubishi motors and mercedesbenz in the automotive 
sector mitsubishi electric and aeg in electrical systems and 
components mitsubishi heavy industries and deutsche aerospace in 
aircraft and aerospace equipment and mitsubishi corp and 
daimlerbenz inter services in trading and investment services 
mori said the weekend meeting evolved from a meeting last 
november in europe between mitsubishi corp president shinroku 
morohashi and daimler benz chairman edzard reuter morohashi was in 
europe to mark the offering of mitsubishi shares on the london and 
paris stock exchanges mori said 
morohashi and reuter led their companies executives at the 
singapore meeting the spokesman said 
mitsubishi corp is the core company of the giant mitsubishi 
group of related firms and is japans largest trading company with 
